dcterms:description: ACE 2005 stands out as the most widely-used dataset for event detection, drawing from a diverse array of news sources spanning 6 distinct categories. It includes types and 33 more finely-grained annotations for 8 event subtypes.
dcterms:title: ACE 2005

dcterms:description: FewEvent currently stands as the largest few-shot dataset for event detection, covering 19 event types, which are further subdivided into 100 event subtypes.
dcterms:title: FewEvent
